<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1399,1457,1554]" box="[189,1399,1457,1484]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<keyLead box="[189,1399,1457,1484]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">1 Uniformly yellow; HW&lt;0.55; PI&lt;40; IOD&lt;0.45..............................................................................2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1399,1457,1554]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<keyLead pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
– Uniformly brown or blackish brown species; HW&gt;0.60; PI&gt;45; IOD&gt;0.55 (
<collectingCountry box="[1129,1390,1492,1519]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">United Arab Emirates</collectingCountry>
) .............................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Agosti &amp; Collingwood, 2011)" authorityName="Sharaf &amp; Akbar &amp; Al Dhafer &amp; Aldawood" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Agosti &amp; Collingwood" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[806,1264,1527,1554]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Temnothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="liviae" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[806,900,1527,1554]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">T. liviae</emphasis>
(Agosti &amp; 
<bibRefCitation author="Collingwood C. A. &amp; Agosti D. &amp; Sharaf M. R. &amp; van Harten A." box="[1030,1256,1528,1554]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="405 - 474" refId="ref6228" refString="Collingwood C. A., Agosti D., Sharaf M. R. &amp; van Harten A. 2011. Order Hymenoptera, Family Formicidae. In: van Harten A. (ed.) Arthropod Fauna of the UAE 4: 405 - 474. Dar Al Ummah, Abu Dhabi." type="journal article" year="2011">Collingwood, 2011</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1270,1399,1528,1554]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1399,1593,1901]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<keyStep pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<keyLead pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
2 Cephalic dorsum nearly smooth and shiny with feeble longitudinal striae in full-face view; frontal carinae feeble, running back to anterior level of eyes; propodeal spines short and blunt; petiole with a single pair of distinctly erect hairs; mesosomal dorsum feebly, longitudinally, rugose on pronotum and mesonotum, reticulate on propodeum. (
<collectingCountry box="[880,955,1699,1725]" name="Sudan" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Sudan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1016,1278,1699,1726]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">United Arab Emirates</collectingCountry>
) .............. ............................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hamann &amp; Klemm, 1967) Cephalic" authorityName="Cephalic" baseAuthorityName="Hamann &amp; Klemm" baseAuthorityYear="1967" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Temnothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megalops">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[909,1057,1733,1760]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">T. megalops</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hamann H. H. F. &amp; Klemm W." box="[1076,1390,1734,1761]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="411 - 421" refId="ref6564" refString="Hamann H. H. F. &amp; Klemm W. 1967. Ergebnisse der zoologischen Nubien-Expedition 1962. Teil XXXIV. Hymenoptera - Formicidae. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien 70: 411 - 421." type="journal article" year="1967">Hamann &amp; Klemm, 1967</bibRefCitation>
) 
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1399,1593,1901]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<keyLead pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Cephalic dorsum strongly, longitudinally, irregularly striate in full-face view; frontal carinae more developed, running back to midlevel of eyes; propodeal spines long and sharp; petiole with two pairs of normal hairs; mesosoma weakly reticulate-rugose. (
<collectingCountry box="[1109,1171,1840,1866]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">KSA</collectingCountry>
) ............................ ............................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Sharaf &amp; Akbar" authorityName="Sharaf &amp; Akbar &amp; Al Dhafer &amp; Aldawood" authorityYear="2017" box="[909,1279,1874,1901]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Temnothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arabicus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[909,1054,1874,1901]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">T. arabicus</emphasis>
Sharaf &amp; Akbar
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1297,1399,1875,1901]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
